# Code owners for security-sensitive review machinery.
#
# These paths define the criteria and prompts that gate every PR. A change to
# them changes what the review agents and CI accept, so they require explicit
# owner review. Refs #1967.
#
# Note: the former `.claude/review-axes/` was moved to
# `.claude/skills/review/references/` in PR #2043; pin the current path.

# Canonical /review axis criteria (CI prompts are generated from these).
/.claude/skills/review/references/        @rjmurillo

# Generated CI review prompts (pr-quality gate, per role).
/.github/prompts/pr-quality-gate-*.md     @rjmurillo
/.github/prompts/pr-quality.*.prompt.md   @rjmurillo

# Shared library backing the AI review gates. The canonical package lives under
# scripts/; .claude/lib/ is the synced copy (scripts/sync_plugin_lib.py). Pin
# both so gate-logic changes (verdict.py merge rules) cannot bypass owner review.
/scripts/ai_review_common/                @rjmurillo
/.claude/lib/ai_review_common/            @rjmurillo
